						<summary>

						<p>The inscription belongs to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Akaḷaṅkacharita Iṟivabeḍaṅga Satyāśraya</hi> and registers gifts of land made to certain local religious institutions, by the king's officer <hi rend="bold">Seṭṭi Brahmayya</hi> who was administering <hi rend="bold">Tuṁbagi,</hi> an <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> in <hi rend="bold">Pagalaṭṭi Three Hundred</hi> and by a lady named <hi rend="bold">Āychakabbe,</hi> with rules for their management.</p>						

						<p>The record is <hi rend="bold">dated in Śaka 926, Krōdhin, Āshāḍha, amāvāsyā, solar eclipse.</hi> The date corresponds to <hi rend="bold">Thursday, July 20, A.D. 1004.</hi></p>						

						<p>(Published in <hi rend="italic">Ep. Ind.,</hi> Vol. XVII, p. 7<note n="36-1">In l. 24 of the text Goṇnayya</note>).</p>						

						</summary>
